I see! The `parseStringJsonSchema` only handles `maxLength`, `minLength`, and `pattern`, but it ignores `format`. So when the JSON Schema has `format: "email"`, the `@ark/json-schema` parser doesn't convert it to an ArkType email keyword.

But also, the `pattern` field IS being handled. The JSON Schema output has `"pattern": "^[\\w%+.-]+@[\\d.A-Za-z-]+\\.[A-Za-z]{2,}$"`. However, the round-tripped type still accepts "not-an-email". 

Wait, let me look more carefully at the issue. The JSON Schema output is:
```json
{
  "$schema": "https://json-schema.org/draft/2020-12/schema",
  "type": "string",
  "pattern": "^[\\w%+.-]+@[\\d.A-Za-z-]+\\.[A-Za-z]{2,}$",
  "format": "email"
}
